@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix sssom: <https://w3id.org/sssom/schema/> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix xwkont-source-term: <https://w3id.org/xwkont/source-term#> .

<https://w3id.org/xwkont/id#mapping:event:001> a sssom:Mapping ;
    rdfs:comment "Both are explicit, named top-level Event categories, both now directly verified; UFO continues DOLCE's lineage (per `continuant-occurrent.md` mapping-004). Not `exact-equivalence-candidate` because UFO's event theory (mereology, causation, modal fragility) is more elaborated than DOLCE's Achievement/Accomplishment split."@en ;
    sssom:confidence 1e+00 ;
    sssom:mapping_justification "semapv:ManualMappingCuration" ;
    sssom:object_id xwkont-source-term:UFO-Event ;
    sssom:predicate_id skos:closeMatch ;
    sssom:subject_id xwkont-source-term:DOLCE-Event .

<https://w3id.org/xwkont/id#mapping:event:002> a sssom:Mapping ;
    rdfs:comment "Structural mismatch: BFO's Process is temporally extended and sits opposite Process Boundary, not opposite a Stative/Event split. Whether BFO:Process better corresponds to DOLCE:Stative or DOLCE:Event (or neither cleanly) is unresolved."@en ;
    sssom:confidence 2e-01 ;
    sssom:mapping_justification "semapv:ManualMappingCuration" ;
    sssom:object_id xwkont-source-term:DOLCE-Event ;
    sssom:subject_id xwkont-source-term:BFO-Process .

<https://w3id.org/xwkont/id#mapping:event:003> a sssom:Mapping ;
    rdfs:comment "Both isolate an atomic/instantaneous occurrent, per `note-002`, now on verified primary-source definitions for both sides — but from structurally different hierarchies and not confirmed by a source making this comparison explicitly, so confidence is not raised past medium."@en ;
    sssom:confidence 6e-01 ;
    sssom:mapping_justification "semapv:ManualMappingCuration" ;
    sssom:object_id xwkont-source-term:DOLCE-Achievement ;
    sssom:predicate_id skos:closeMatch ;
    sssom:subject_id xwkont-source-term:BFO-Process_Boundary .

<https://w3id.org/xwkont/id#mapping:event:004> a sssom:Mapping ;
    rdfs:comment "SUMO nests this inside Process rather than treating it as a parallel category; correspondence is exploratory only."@en ;
    sssom:confidence 2e-01 ;
    sssom:mapping_justification "semapv:ManualMappingCuration" ;
    sssom:object_id xwkont-source-term:SUMO-IntentionalProcess_LifeEvent ;
    sssom:subject_id xwkont-source-term:UFO-Event .

<https://w3id.org/xwkont/id#mapping:event:005> a sssom:Mapping ;
    rdfs:comment "Both isolate an atomic/instantaneous occurrent (per `note-005`, extending `note-002`) — GFO's own text glosses this technical sense as \"instantaneous event.\" Structurally different hierarchies (GFO: subtype of `Change`; DOLCE: subtype of `Event`), and no source draws this comparison itself, so capped at medium like `event-003`."@en ;
    sssom:confidence 6e-01 ;
    sssom:mapping_justification "semapv:ManualMappingCuration" ;
    sssom:object_id xwkont-source-term:DOLCE-Achievement ;
    sssom:predicate_id skos:closeMatch ;
    sssom:subject_id xwkont-source-term:GFO-Instantaneous_change .

<https://w3id.org/xwkont/id#mapping:event:006> a sssom:Mapping ;
    rdfs:comment "Same atomic/instantaneous convergence as `event-005`, now against BFO's own Process Boundary sibling class — a three-way convergence per `note-005`."@en ;
    sssom:confidence 6e-01 ;
    sssom:mapping_justification "semapv:ManualMappingCuration" ;
    sssom:object_id xwkont-source-term:BFO-Process_Boundary ;
    sssom:predicate_id skos:closeMatch ;
    sssom:subject_id xwkont-source-term:GFO-Instantaneous_change .

<https://w3id.org/xwkont/id#mapping:event:007> a sssom:Mapping ;
    rdfs:comment "Both give a positive, named process/event distinction rather than treating \"event\" as a synonym or umbrella term — YAMATO's \"events are made of processes... processes can change, events cannot\" parallels DOLCE's cumulative/non-cumulative criterion in spirit, though the two criteria are not formally identical and YAMATO's own OWL is not fetched (quotation-only citation). Not `high` because the underlying formalizations were not directly compared class-for-class."@en ;
    sssom:confidence 8e-01 ;
    sssom:mapping_justification "semapv:ManualMappingCuration" ;
    sssom:object_id xwkont-source-term:DOLCE-Event ;
    sssom:predicate_id skos:closeMatch ;
    sssom:subject_id xwkont-source-term:YAMATO-Event .

<https://w3id.org/xwkont/id#mapping:event:008> a sssom:Mapping ;
    rdfs:comment "YAMATO's \"events... cannot change\" criterion echoes UFO's characterization of events as \"modally fragile entities\" that \"cannot genuinely change... while maintaining their numerical identity\" — a substantive terminological and conceptual convergence between two independently-authored sources, not just a shared label."@en ;
    sssom:confidence 8e-01 ;
    sssom:mapping_justification "semapv:ManualMappingCuration" ;
    sssom:object_id xwkont-source-term:UFO-Event ;
    sssom:predicate_id skos:closeMatch ;
    sssom:subject_id xwkont-source-term:YAMATO-Event .

xwkont-source-term:BFO-Process rdfs:label "Process"@en ;
    dcterms:source "BFO" .

xwkont-source-term:SUMO-IntentionalProcess_LifeEvent rdfs:label "IntentionalProcess/LifeEvent"@en ;
    dcterms:source "SUMO" .

xwkont-source-term:BFO-Process_Boundary rdfs:label "Process Boundary"@en ;
    dcterms:source "BFO" .

xwkont-source-term:DOLCE-Achievement rdfs:label "Achievement"@en ;
    dcterms:source "DOLCE" .

xwkont-source-term:GFO-Instantaneous_change rdfs:label "Instantaneous_change"@en ;
    dcterms:source "GFO" .

xwkont-source-term:YAMATO-Event rdfs:label "Event"@en ;
    dcterms:source "YAMATO" .

xwkont-source-term:DOLCE-Event rdfs:label "Event"@en ;
    dcterms:source "DOLCE" .

xwkont-source-term:UFO-Event rdfs:label "Event"@en ;
    dcterms:source "UFO" .

